item.title: [HBASE-8918] Removes redundant identifiers from interfaces
item.description:
A lot of interfaces in HBase's source have things like "public" or "abstract" modifiers which make no sense. They add to visual clutter, generate warnings in lots of IDEs and serve no purpose.

This is a patch that just removes them all. I understand that it's touching a lot of files etc. Your call if you want this kind of patch.

-  public static final boolean SPLIT_SKIP_ERRORS_DEFAULT = false;

removing public from interfaces used by coprocessors (e.g. requestCompaction methods) can also have undesirable effects.
Everything in interfaces is public by default, isn't it?
Well, they are classes, actually, so it becomes package private. I was thinking of InterfaceVisibility attribute...
